    "body": "This doesn't seem particularly difficult, so could submit PR, even if it takes me a while.\r\n\r\n[This block](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/f14047dae57aa69e4fa08d57e19ee9c0283dfa54/eth/backend.go#L386) puts a lower limit on \"regular\" peers, to be 1/2 of `maxpeers`.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nWhat would be a reasonable approach and option name?\r\n\r\n* Limit \"regular\" peers with `--maxfullpeers`? Or name it `--fullpeers`? `--heavypeers`?..\r\n* Rework `--lightpeers` to mean \"dedicated light client slots\"?\r\n* Allow specifying `--minfullpeers`?\r\n* Something else?",
